a shitload of them back in WWII.

45:56.960 --> 45:59.349
They're like tranquillisers,

45:59.440 --> 46:04.673
only they break the skin's surface enough
to cause blood but no real damage.

46:04.760 --> 46:08.036
So it looks like
the person's been shot and killed

46:08.120 --> 46:11.430
and really they're just
unconscious and bleeding?

46:11.520 --> 46:13.112
Oh.

46:13.200 --> 46:14.997
Right.

46:15.080 --> 46:19.153
See, we shoot Kurt and Ram,
make it look like they shot each other

46:19.240 --> 46:24.189
and by the time they regain consciousness,
they'll be the laughing stock of the school.

46:24.280 --> 46:27.397
The note's the punch line.
How'd that turn out?

46:27.480 --> 46:30.597
First tell me the similarity is not incredible.

46:32.000 --> 46:33.752
It's incredible similarity.

46:35.960 --> 46:37.996
OK. Ahem.

46:39.680 --> 46:41.750
"Ram and I died the day we realised

46:41.840 --> 46:46.311
"we could never reveal our forbidden love
to an uncaring and un-understanding world.

46:46.400 --> 46:50.518
"The joy we shared in each other's arms
was greater than any touchdown,

46:50.600 --> 46:52.750
"yet we were forced to live the lie

46:52.840 --> 46:56.230
"of sexist, beer-guzzling, jock assholes."

46:56.320 --> 46:58.550
That's perfect.

46:58.640 --> 47:02.110
Let's take a look at some
of the homosexual artefacts

47:02.200 --> 47:04.156
I dug up to plant at the scene.

47:05.840 --> 47:08.559
All right. An issue of Stud Puppy.

47:08.640 --> 47:11.154
That's great!

47:11.240 --> 47:15.518
A candy dish, a Joan Crawford postcard.

47:15.600 --> 47:17.511
Good.

47:17.600 --> 47:19.556
Some mascara.

47:20.720 --> 47:25.316
All right, now, here's the one perfecto thing
I picked up -

47:25.400 --> 47:26.549
mineral water.

47:26.640 --> 47:31.475
Come on, a lot of people
drink mineral water. It's come a long way.

47:31.560 --> 47:33.278
Yeah, but this is Ohio.

47:33.360 --> 47:36.955
If you don't have a brewski in your hand,
you might as well be wearing a dress.

47:37.040 --> 47:39.235
Oh, you're so smart.

47:49.880 --> 47:51.950
Hi, Veronica.

47:52.040 --> 47:53.951
Hi, guys.

47:56.080 --> 47:58.116
Glad you could make it.

48:06.400 --> 48:08.516
So should I just whip it out or...

48:08.600 --> 48:12.639
Well, I've made a circle
on each side of the clearing.

48:12.720 --> 48:15.154
Ram, you come over here.

48:15.240 --> 48:16.673
Kurt.

48:18.520 --> 48:21.796
When you get to the circle, strip.

48:21.880 --> 48:23.836
What about you?

48:23.920 --> 48:27.276
I was hoping you could
rip my clothes off me, sport.

48:28.800 --> 48:30.153
Oh.

48:30.240 --> 48:31.878
Good idea.

48:39.920 --> 48:43.071
OK. Count of three, guys.

48:45.000 --> 48:46.638
One...

48:49.280 --> 48:50.998
two...

48:52.560 --> 48:55.313
Three!

48:57.800 --> 48:59.756
You missed him completely?

48:59.840 --> 49:01.831
It was worth it just to see the look...

49:01.920 --> 49:04.798
Don't move. I'll get him back.

49:41.000 --> 49:42.752
Ha!

50:10.720 --> 50:12.711
- No.
- Now!

50:23.800 --> 50:26.360
- Hey, I heard it that time.
- What?

50:26.440 --> 50:28.510
Another gunshot from the woods.

50:28.600 --> 50:30.556
Oh, shit. Let's roll!

50:30.640 --> 50:32.517
Kurt doesn't look too good.

50:32.600 --> 50:34.716
Just remember he's left-handed.

50:34.800 --> 50:38.076
Keep going until you hit the clearing.

50:38.160 --> 50:40.276
Come on.

50:44.360 --> 50:46.715
- Mother of shit!
- Call in.

50:46.800 --> 50:51.112
Hey, I heard something out there.

50:51.200 --> 50:53.156
I'm checking it out.

50:53.240 --> 50:56.869
This is Officer McCord.
I've got two dead bodies in the woods

50:56.960 --> 50:58.712
behind Westerburg High.

51:29.520 --> 51:31.476
Whoa! Whoa!

51:44.920 --> 51:48.799
'Milner, can you hear me?
What's going down? '

51:48.880 --> 51:52.589
Yeah... I think what I heard
was just a bunny rabbit.

51:52.680 --> 51:56.355
All I've got here is two kids
making out in a station wagon.

51:56.440 --> 51:58.317
'Should I pry them apart? '

51:58.400 --> 52:01.551
No. Forget it.
I got all the answers back here.

52:01.640 --> 52:03.278
Hey...

52:03.360 --> 52:05.920
are they naked?

52:17.240 --> 52:19.879
Yeah, so what's the deal?

52:19.960 --> 52:23.475
Suicide. Double suicide.
They shot each other.

52:23.560 --> 52:25.596
Hey, that's Kurt Kelly.

52:25.680 --> 52:28.069
Yeah, and the linebacker, Ram Sweeney.

52:30.000 --> 52:33.629
Phew. My God, suicide. Why?

52:34.920 --> 52:37.912
Does this answer your question?

52:38.000 --> 52:40.309
Oh, man. They were fags.

52:40.400 --> 52:45.030
Listen up. "We realised we could never
reveal our forbidden love

52:45.120 --> 52:48.430
"to an uncaring
and un-understanding world."

52:48.520 --> 52:51.193
Jesus H Christ!

52:51.280 --> 52:54.113
The quarterback buggering the linebacker.

52:55.200 --> 52:57.111
What a waste.

52:57.200 --> 52:59.156
Oh, the humanity.

53:33.160 --> 53:35.469
So we killed them, didn't we?

53:35.560 --> 53:37.676
Yeah. Of course.

54:02.760 --> 54:06.230
Echt Luger bullets. I'm such an idiot.

54:09.280 --> 54:12.989
Look, you believed it
because you wanted to believe it.

54:13.080 --> 54:17.835
Your true feelings
were too gross and icky for you to face.

54:19.120 --> 54:21.953
I did not want them dead.

54:23.520 --> 54:26.557
- You did too.
- I did not.

54:26.640 --> 54:27.868
Did too.

54:27.960 --> 54:29.279
- I did not.
- Did too.

54:29.360 --> 54:31.191
- Did not.
- Did too.

54:31.280 --> 54:33.475
- Did not! Did not!
- Did too!

54:33.560 --> 54:35.630
Shut up! I did not want them dead.

54:35.720 --> 54:39.030
- Come on, you did. You're just...
- # Mary had a little lamb... #

54:39.120 --> 54:42.669
I did not!

54:43.920 --> 54:45.512
Young love!

54:45.600 --> 54:49.354
School's cancelled today
because Kurt and Ram killed themselves

54:49.440 --> 54:51.431
in a repressed homosexual suicide pact!

54:51.520 --> 54:53.476
No way.

54:55.560 --> 54:57.312
God!

54:58.880 --> 55:02.270
The football season is over, Veronica.

55:02.360 --> 55:05.113
Kurt and Ram
had nothing to offer the school

55:05.200 --> 55:07.236
but date rapes and AIDS jokes.

55:08.680 --> 55:10.750
Sure.

55:11.960 --> 55:14.952
Can we make an ice run
before the funeral?

55:21.200 --> 55:24.237
If there's any way
you can hear me, Kurt buddy...

55:26.800 --> 55:30.270
I don't care that
you really were some... pansy.

55:31.920 --> 55:33.911
You're my own flesh and blood

55:34.000 --> 55:35.956
and you made me proud.

55:38.520 --> 55:41.432
My son's a homosexual and I love him.

55:43.800 --> 55:45.756
I love my dead, gay son.

55:47.040 --> 55:51.989
How do you think he'd react to a son
that had a limp wrist with a pulse?

56:08.000 --> 56:13.438
'Dear diary, my teen angst bullshit
has a body count.

56:13.520 --> 56:16.671
'The most popular people
in school are dead.

56:16.760 --> 56:21.356
'Everybody's sad
but it's a weird kind of sad.

56:21.440 --> 56:26.594
'Suicide gave Heather depth,
Kurt a soul, Ram a brain.

56:27.720 --> 56:29.676
'I don't know what it's given me

56:29.760 --> 56:34.311
'but I've got no control
over myself when I'm with JD.

56:34.400 --> 56:37.278
'Are we going to prom or to hell? '

56:37.360 --> 56:42.275
Now, it seems we were in
a similar position on Monday

56:42.360 --> 56:45.397
when I thoughtfully suggested
we get everybody together

56:45.480 --> 56:48.517
for an unadulterated
emotional outpouring, but no.

56:48.600 --> 56:52.559
You took this as an opportunity
to play yet another round

56:52.640 --> 56:54.915
of "let's laugh at the hippy".

56:55.000 --> 56:58.390
- Pauline...
- Shut up, Paul.

56:58.480 --> 57:00.675
I've seen a lot of bullshit -

57:00.760 --> 57:03.274
ángel dust, switchblades,

57:03.360 --> 57:07.353
sexually perverse photography exhibits
involving tennis rackets -

57:07.440 --> 57:09.556
but this suicide thing...

57:10.840 --> 57:14.799
guess that's more on Pauline's wavelength.

57:14.880 --> 57:17.553
We're just going to write off today

57:17.640 --> 57:23.033
and on Friday she can hold
her little love-in or whatever.

57:24.480 --> 57:26.232
Whatever.

57:31.840 --> 57:33.239
Attention!

57:34.680 --> 57:37.240
May I have your attention, please?

57:37.320 --> 57:41.359
This school has been
torn apart by tragedy.

57:41.440 --> 57:45.149
I'm here today to fuse it back again
through togetherness.

57:45.240 --> 57:48.596
I want everyone to clasp hands.

57:48.680 --> 57:52.389
We need to connect this cafeteria
into one mighty circuit!

57:52.480 --> 57:55.392
- Excuse me.
- Here comes the TV crew!

57:55.480 --> 57:57.232
Lock your paws!

57:57.320 --> 57:59.959
- We're ready when you are.
- Hi, there.

58:01.000 --> 58:04.993
Come on. Let's go. Here.

58:05.080 --> 58:07.913
This will be on TV.
Let's show them how you feel!

58:08.000 --> 58:11.390
Looks like Miss Phlegm's
on another one of her crusades.

58:11.480 --> 58:13.550
With usual success, of course.

58:13.640 --> 58:15.392
Come on, get up!

58:15.480 --> 58:17.118
Hi, what's your name?

58:17.200 --> 58:18.997
I'm Heather Duke.

58:24.520 --> 58:27.910
Is this as good for you as it is for me?

58:28.000 --> 58:30.639
Those fish sticks can wait. Let's go.

58:30.720 --> 58:32.676
Come on, kids!

58:34.520 --> 58:36.795
The whole world is watching!

58:39.120 --> 58:41.315
Show them that you care!

58:42.400 --> 58:45.039
Greetings and salutations.

58:45.120 --> 58:49.875
I'll need a VHS copy of this by Monday
for my Princeton application.

58:51.280 --> 58:54.909
You can beat this,
don't let suicide get you down.

58:56.200 --> 58:58.668
That thing this afternoon,

58:58.760 --> 59:01.513
I'm so angry, it was chaos, fucking chaos.

59:02.960 --> 59:04.837
What are you talking about?

59:04.920 --> 59:08.629
I mean, today was great.
Chaos was great.

59:08.720 --> 59:12.030
Chaos is what killed the dinosaurs, darling.

59:13.320 --> 59:15.436
Face it, our way is the way.

59:15.520 --> 59:17.954
We scare people into not being assholes.

59:18.040 --> 59:20.634
Our way is not our way.

59:20.720 --> 59:23.553
Oh, yeah? Tell that to the judge, all right?

59:23.640 --> 59:25.471
Tell it to Kurt Kelly.

59:25.560 --> 59:27.915
I'm telling it to you.

59:30.280 --> 59:32.350
God, you can be so immature.

59:32.440 --> 59:36.035
Oh! You kids are making
too much damn noise.

59:37.680 --> 59:39.750
We beat the bitches.

59:39.840 --> 59:42.308
Beautiful. The beaver's home.

59:42.400 --> 59:45.358
Judge told them to slurp shit and die.

59:45.440 --> 59:48.955
I put a Norwegian in the boiler room.

59:49.040 --> 59:51.429
Masterful.

59:51.520 --> 59:54.353
And then when that blew,

59:54.440 --> 59:57.591
it set off a pack of thermals I stuck upstairs.

01:00:07.280 --> 01:00:09.589
Some days it's great to be alive.

01:00:12.040 --> 01:00:14.429
Stick it to those goddamn...

01:00:14.520 --> 01:00:16.476
Do you like your father?

01:00:17.920 --> 01:00:20.354
Never given the matter much thought.

01:00:23.240 --> 01:00:25.196
Liked my mother.

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:29.072
They said her death was an accident

01:00:29.160 --> 01:00:31.993
but she knew what she was doing.

01:00:32.080 --> 01:00:36.949
She walked into the building two minutes
before my dad blew the place up.

01:00:37.040 --> 01:00:40.191
She waved at me and then...

01:00:40.280 --> 01:00:42.236
boom.

01:00:42.320 --> 01:00:46.108
'Dudes, if I get one more request
for that Big Fun song,

01:00:46.200 --> 01:00:47.918
'I'm gonna commit suicide.'

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:49.752
Playing our song.

01:00:49.840 --> 01:00:52.479
'Here it is, Teenage Suicide Don't Do It.'

01:00:53.960 --> 01:00:57.236
# Teenage suicide
# Don't do it

01:00:57.320 --> 01:00:59.788
# Teenage suicide
# She blew it

01:00:59.880 --> 01:01:01.950
# Teenage suicide

01:01:02.040 --> 01:01:03.314
# Don't do it... #

01:01:05.880 --> 01:01:07.916
That's it. We're breaking up.

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:11.310
What? You can't bring them back,
you must know that.

01:01:11.400 --> 01:01:15.439
I'm not trying to bring anybody back
except maybe myself.

01:01:26.080 --> 01:01:27.911
No!

01:01:29.400 --> 01:01:32.198
To think once
I actually thought you were cool.

01:01:32.280 --> 01:01:36.717
If you can't deal with me now
then just stay home and shoot your TV,

01:01:36.800 --> 01:01:39.394
blow up a couple toasters or something.

01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:43.553
Just don't come to school
and don't mess with me.

01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:48.151
You'll be back.

01:01:59.720 --> 01:02:02.029
Me and Martha Dumptruck?

01:02:02.120 --> 01:02:03.917
Where did you get this?

01:02:05.080 --> 01:02:09.437
Oh, I just had the nicest little chat
with Ms Dumptruck.

01:02:09.520 --> 01:02:11.556
Got along famously.

01:02:11.640 --> 01:02:14.996
It's scary how everybody's got
a little story to tell.

01:02:15.080 --> 01:02:17.514
Want to see the canoeing shots?

01:02:17.600 --> 01:02:19.431
What is this? Blackmail?

01:02:23.520 --> 01:02:25.670
I'll give you a week's lunch money.

01:02:27.840 --> 01:02:31.549
I don't want your money.
I want your strength.

01:02:31.640 --> 01:02:34.677
Westerburg does not need
mushy togetherness,

01:02:34.760 --> 01:02:36.955
it needs a strong leader.

01:02:37.040 --> 01:02:40.077
Heather Chandler was that leader but...

01:02:40.160 --> 01:02:42.549
But she couldn't handle it.

01:02:42.640 --> 01:02:44.631
I think you can.

01:02:45.720 --> 01:02:47.676
Moby Dick is dunked.

01:02:47.760 --> 01:02:52.436
The white whale drank some bad plankton
and splashed through a coffee table

01:02:52.520 --> 01:02:55.159
and now it's your turn to take the helm.

01:02:55.240 --> 01:02:57.356
What about the photographs?

01:02:57.440 --> 01:03:00.876
Oh, don't worry.
I'll ask you to do me a favour

01:03:00.960 --> 01:03:03.030
and it'll be one you'll enjoy.

01:03:03.120 --> 01:03:05.714
You'll get the negatives back then.

01:03:08.080 --> 01:03:11.550
But in the meantime, strength.

01:03:13.320 --> 01:03:15.390
Here's a little gift...

01:03:16.480 --> 01:03:18.630
from Heather to Heather.

01:03:58.400 --> 01:03:59.992
- Guess who.
- Heather?

01:04:18.120 --> 01:04:19.439
'Hello? '

01:04:19.520 --> 01:04:21.158
Hello, Betty? This is Veronica.

01:04:24.840 --> 01:04:27.400
I don't believe it, I'm winning!

01:04:28.720 --> 01:04:31.473
Don't you start getting cocky on me, girl.

01:04:33.240 --> 01:04:35.470
I really missed you.

01:04:35.560 --> 01:04:38.597
I know I'm not as exciting as
your other friends.

01:04:38.680 --> 01:04:40.636
That is bullshit.

01:04:40.720 --> 01:04:42.676
Shoot.

01:04:42.760 --> 01:04:45.035
Do you know I'm still a virgin?

01:04:45.120 --> 01:04:48.192
OK, I French-kissed Al Springer once.

01:04:48.280 --> 01:04:50.236
It was a total disaster.

01:04:50.320 --> 01:04:53.232
Shoot the ball.

01:04:55.760 --> 01:05:00.629
Betty, your daydreams are a lot better than
my realities, believe me.

01:05:03.200 --> 01:05:06.272
But now, prepare to die.

01:05:06.360 --> 01:05:08.112
Ronnie.

01:05:23.240 --> 01:05:25.993
You're not just going for those two shots.

01:05:26.080 --> 01:05:29.709
I mean, go ahead, knock me out.
It's the only way to win.

01:05:31.400 --> 01:05:33.675
It's not my style.

01:05:33.760 --> 01:05:37.514
Nice guys finish last, I should know.

01:05:46.160 --> 01:05:47.513
Bravo.

01:05:48.600 --> 01:05:50.318
Bravo.

01:05:51.400 --> 01:05:53.960
Listen, I got to get home, OK?

01:05:54.040 --> 01:05:56.156
OK.

01:05:56.240 --> 01:05:58.037
Thanks.

01:05:58.120 --> 01:05:59.997
Bye, Betty.

01:06:00.080 --> 01:06:01.513
Bye.

01:06:01.600 --> 01:06:04.512
Betty, leaving so soon?

01:06:04.600 --> 01:06:06.158
I'm red.

01:06:33.480 --> 01:06:37.553
'The Westerburg suicides
were tough on all of us,

01:06:37.640 --> 01:06:42.350
'but we shared the pain of losing
three very popular students.

01:06:42.440 --> 01:06:46.069
'I came into the cafeteria,
asked them to hold hands... '

01:06:46.160 --> 01:06:48.993
Isn't that that flake
we met at the open house?

01:06:49.080 --> 01:06:51.389
'... burst of cleansing synchronicity,

01:06:51.480 --> 01:06:54.870
'TV cameras happened
onto our path and captured... '

01:06:54.960 --> 01:06:57.520
Cleansing synchronicity?

01:06:57.600 --> 01:07:01.388
Outpouring of emotion?

01:07:01.480 --> 01:07:03.789
Ha! Look! There's Heather.

01:07:05.040 --> 01:07:07.713
There's Heather. Where are you, Veronica?

01:07:07.800 --> 01:07:13.511
'Before a teenager decides to kill himself,
there are certain facts that he should know.

01:07:13.600 --> 01:07:19.391
'After all, this decision affects all of us
and there's only one chance to get it right.'

01:07:32.240 --> 01:07:34.196
'Getting some supervi... '

01:07:34.280 --> 01:07:36.111
Turn that back on.

01:07:36.200 --> 01:07:38.509
These programmes are eating suicide up.

01:07:38.600 --> 01:07:41.433
They're making it sound like
a cool thing to do.

01:07:41.520 --> 01:07:46.469
Are you trying to tell me it's not a time
for troubled youth? Stand up straight.

01:07:46.560 --> 01:07:49.757
All we want is to be
treated like human beings,

01:07:49.840 --> 01:07:52.354
not patronised like bunny rabbits.

01:07:52.440 --> 01:07:54.590
I don't patronise bunny rabbits.

01:07:54.680 --> 01:07:56.671
Treated like human beings?

01:07:56.760 --> 01:08:00.514
Is that what you said,
little Miss Voice-of-a-generation?

01:08:00.600 --> 01:08:03.831
How do you think adults
act with other adults?

01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:06.593
You think it's all just
a game of doubles tennis?

01:08:06.680 --> 01:08:10.116
When teenagers complain
they want to be treated like human beings,

01:08:10.200 --> 01:08:12.998
it's because they are
being treated like human beings.

01:08:13.080 --> 01:08:17.551
Well, I guess I picked the wrong time
to be a human being.

01:08:17.640 --> 01:08:19.631
Well, you'll live.

01:08:25.760 --> 01:08:27.716
Want some pâté?

01:08:29.800 --> 01:08:32.234
Hi, everybody. Door was open.

01:08:32.319 --> 01:08:34.675
Veronica, have you heard?

01:08:34.760 --> 01:08:37.115
We were doing Chinese at the food fair

01:08:37.200 --> 01:08:40.510
when we heard Martha Dumptruck
tried to buy the farm.

01:08:40.600 --> 01:08:44.434
She belly-flopped in front of a car
wearing a suicide note.

01:08:45.439 --> 01:08:47.192
Is she dead?

01:08:47.279 --> 01:08:50.955
No. That's the punch line.
She's in stable condition.

01:08:51.040 --> 01:08:56.068
Just another case of a geek trying to imitate
the popular people and failing miserably.

01:08:56.160 --> 01:08:58.116
Is that pâté?

01:09:02.160 --> 01:09:05.630
- I said I was sorry.
- You were out of control.

01:09:05.720 --> 01:09:08.792
Heather and Kurt were a shock
but Martha Dumptruck?

01:09:08.880 --> 01:09:11.997
Get crucial. She dialled
suicide hotlines in her diapers.

01:09:12.080 --> 01:09:14.196
You're not funny.

01:09:15.240 --> 01:09:19.438
Look, Martha couldn't take the heat
so she got out of the kitchen.

01:09:19.520 --> 01:09:24.229
Just think what a better place this world
would be if every nimrod followed her cue.

01:09:24.319 --> 01:09:27.198
Just shut up. Hot Probs is on.

01:09:27.279 --> 01:09:28.759
Oh, shit. Yeah.

01:09:28.840 --> 01:09:33.356
'Skipper's OK but sometimes
