can think to bring upon itself.

01:19:33.720 --> 01:19:38.157
Nobody's going to care about
exact handwriting. Help me. Quick.

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:50.230
Life sucks.

01:19:53.360 --> 01:19:55.316
It's perfecto.

01:19:56.440 --> 01:20:00.115
Jesus, I've got
a meaningfully marked-up Moby Dick.

01:20:00.200 --> 01:20:02.555
What else does a suicide need, huh?

01:20:02.640 --> 01:20:04.596
Now, if you'll excuse me.

01:20:09.840 --> 01:20:11.592
No!

01:20:17.760 --> 01:20:19.716
Open the door!

01:20:27.400 --> 01:20:29.356
Eskimo.

01:20:33.640 --> 01:20:38.236
Heather Duke underlined a lot of things
in this copy of Moby Dick

01:20:38.320 --> 01:20:42.199
but I believe the word Eskimo,

01:20:42.280 --> 01:20:44.635
underlined all by itself,

01:20:44.720 --> 01:20:48.508
is the key to understanding Heather's pain.

01:20:48.600 --> 01:20:52.593
On the surface, Heather Duke
was the vivacious young lady

01:20:52.680 --> 01:20:54.955
we all knew her to be...

01:20:55.040 --> 01:20:58.669
but her soul was in Antarctica,

01:20:58.760 --> 01:21:04.790
freezing with the knowledge
of the way fellow teenagers can be cruel...

01:21:05.800 --> 01:21:10.635
the way that parents can be unresponsive...

01:21:10.720 --> 01:21:14.998
and as she writes so eloquently
in her suicide note,

01:21:15.080 --> 01:21:18.038
the way that life can suck.

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:23.231
We'll all miss Sherwood's little Eskimo.

01:21:25.480 --> 01:21:29.951
Let's just hope
she's rubbing noses with Jesus.

01:21:30.040 --> 01:21:32.190
